  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Emergency Lifesaving Shelter Assistance to the Displacement Affected Population in hard to reach areas in Borno State, inlcuding Monguno</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at providing lifesaving shelter assistance to the most vulnerable displaced people in Monguno and strengthening the sector capacity by prepositioning shelter Bama type and improved NFIs kit to support timely response by the shelter sector. Responding to the spike in new arrivals, NRC will incorporate safe programming when distributing 650 improved shelters kits and 650 improved NFI kits in Monguno. NRC will target 650 households, representing 3,250 (1,417 M 1,833 F) individuals with improved shelter kits, complemented with NFI kits for each household.. 

Using its community-based approach, NRC will collaborate with traditional leaders and local stakeholders during the project life. To build a sense of ownership and inclusion, NRC will ensure that a community-based beneficiary selection committee will be established and assist in the beneficiary selection using set vulnerability criteria. The committee will be involved in the community sensitisation within the targeted locations, raising awareness of the project and the use of NFI kits among the beneficiaries.

To avoid duplication of efforts, NRC will ensure good coordination with other implementing partners in the targeted locations through active participation in the Shelter/CCCM/NFI Sector.</narrative>
  </description>
